ENTRY            G3149   20260406   20260528   20260528       G060
SUBENT        G3149001   20260406   20260528   20260528       G060
BIB                 16         34
TITLE      Measurement of natNi(g,xn)57,56Ni and natNi(g,pxn)
           58-55Co reaction cross sections in bremsstrahlung with
           end-point energies of 65 and 75 MeV
AUTHOR     (H.Naik, G.N.Kim, T.H.Nguyen, K.Kim, S.G.Shin, Y.U.Kye,
            M.H.Cho)
INSTITUTE  (3INDTRM,3KORKNU,3KORPUE)
REFERENCE  (J,JRN,324,837,2020)
FACILITY   (LINAC,3KORPUE) Pohang Accelerator Laboratory (PAL)
INC-SOURCE (BRST) Pulsed electron beam on thin tungsten target
            (size 10.0 cm x 10.0 cm, thickness 0.1 mm)
SAMPLE     Ni metal foil (purity>99.0%, size: 1.0 cm x 1.0 cm,
            weight of 68.8 mg and 58.6 mg)
METHOD     (ACTIV) Irradiated for 1 hour with the bremsstrahlung
            end-point energies of 65 and 75 MeV (beam current of
            15 mA, 3.75 Hz, pulse length of 1.5 micro-sec)
           (GSPEC) Start after cooling for 10 hours
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Energy resolution of 1.8 keV FWHM at 1332.5
            keV peak of 60Co, and detection efficiency of 20% at
            1332.5 keV relative to a 3 inch diameter x 3 inch
            length NaI(Tl) detector
MONITOR    (13-AL-27(G,X)11-NA-24,,SIG,,BRA)
            - Al foil (purity > 99.98%, thickness: 0.025 mm)
DECAY-MON  (11-NA-24,14.954HR,DG,1368.6,1.00)
MONIT-REF  (,V.Di Napoli+,J,NCL,1,835,1971)
REL-REF    (R,,R.B.Firestone+,B,FIRESTONE,,,1999) WWW Version 2.0,
            Decay data
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty                   (6.5-9.34%)
           (ERR-S,2.,7.) Statistical uncertainty            (2-7%)
           (ERR-1) photon flux                               (~5%)
           (ERR-2) irradiation time                        (~0.5%)
           (ERR-3) gamma-ray detection efficiency            (~3%)
           (ERR-4) half-life and gamma-ray abundance         (~2%)
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by G.N.Kim (2026-04-07)
HISTORY    (20260406C) S.C.Yang
ENDBIB              34
COMMON               4          3
ERR-1      ERR-2      ERR-3      ERR-4
PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT
5.         0.5        3.         2.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           41
